<p>Mick joined Nevo in 2011 from Conservation Services Group (CSG), a leading provider of systems and services that improve residential energy efficiency. 
At CSG he spent almost 15 years defining the requirements for, and leading the team that built complex engineering, analytical, and workflow software. 
Mick’s key strength is rooted in the ability to communicate effectively with all manner of technical and engineering specialists, operating staff, and 
business owners, translating their knowledge into meaningful and productive systems.</p>
<p>At CSG, Mick designed and constructed the core information system systems, managed the software development department, and drove the software 
strategic vision as the company grew from 40 to over 850 people. Starting in the mid 1990’s, Mick developed one of the first mobile field energy analysis system, 
with custom data synchronization to a back-end tracking system; an enterprise-grade CRM, call center, and production/project management system that still manages 
CSG’s large residential energy efficiency business. Most recently, Mick led the team that drove the core business requirements for the development of a 
next-generation residential energy analysis online/in-field application that Nevo built. Prior to working at CSG, Mick developed systems and analytic models 
at Eastern Research Group, primarily for the Environmental Protection Agency.</p>
<p>Mick’s unique combination of engineering, software development, and business experience evolved from a Bachelor’s degree in Mechanical Engineering 
from University College London, and he came to the US in 1990 on a Kennedy Scholarship to do a Masters in Technology and Public Policy at MIT.</p>
